What we need to check in ingress logs to identify the issue ,

{
  "response_code": 500,                 ← ❌ ERROR (backend failure)

  "response_source": "service",         ← 🔥 Error is from backend, NOT ingress

  "service": "perth-service",           ← 🎯 Target service handling request

  "upstream_addr": "172.20.157.217:80",← 📍 Exact backend pod IP

  "uri": "/perth/api/v1/.../cards/...",← 🌐 API endpoint hit

  "method": "GET",                      ← 📥 Request type

  "response_time": 10524,               ← ⏱️ Total time (~10.5 sec)

  "upstream_time": 10522,               ← 🔥 Time spent in backend (very high)

  "upstream_header_time": 10.52,        ← ⏳ Backend took long to respond

  "client_ip": "127.0.0.6",             ← 🌍 Client (internal/proxy)

  "x_forwarded_for": "209.79...",       ← 🌐 Real client IP chain

  "cloudflare_cf_ray": "...",           ← ☁️ Came via Cloudflare

  "olympus_trace_id": "f2f7a284...",    ← 🔗 Trace ID (VERY IMPORTANT)

  "route_name": "perth-service-public-route", ← 🛣️ Routing rule used

  "response_time_secs": 10.524          ← ⏱️ Same latency in seconds
}



